<section><title>pod2docbook script</title>
  <section id="ID-3f9fd1472d4b63414628e99fbbf40a3c"><title>NAME</title>
    <para>
      pod2docbook - Convert POD data to DocBook SGML
    </para>
  </section>
  <section id="ID-c570e7e6895f59333803d984bf8f72cf"><title>SYNOPSIS</title>
    <para>
      pod2docbook [<emphasis role="bold">--help</emphasis>] [<emphasis
      role="bold">--doctype</emphasis>=<emphasis
      role="bold">article</emphasis>|<emphasis
      role="bold">chapter</emphasis>|<emphasis
      role="bold">section</emphasis>|<emphasis
      role="bold">refentry</emphasis>] [<emphasis
      role="bold">--title</emphasis>=<emphasis
      role="italic">title</emphasis>] [<emphasis
      role="bold">--spaces</emphasis>=<emphasis
      role="italic"># spaces per indent level</emphasis>]
      [<emphasis role="bold">--fix-double-quotes</emphasis>] [<emphasis
      role="bold">--no-header</emphasis>] [<emphasis
      role="italic">infile</emphasis> [<emphasis
      role="italic">outfile</emphasis>]]
    </para>
  </section>
  <section id="ID-55a4467b5df1806d79641429c6a6a92d"><title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      <emphasis role="bold">pod2docbook</emphasis> converts files from pod
      format (see <citerefentry> <refentrytitle>perlpod</refentrytitle>
      </citerefentry>) to DocBook 4.2 SGML (see <ulink
      url="http://www.docbook.org/">http://www.docbook.org/</ulink>).  The
      program itself is merely a driver for the Pod::2::DocBook class; if
      you're interested in details of pod-to-SGML translation see
      <citerefentry> <refentrytitle>Pod::2::DocBook</refentrytitle>
      </citerefentry>.
    </para>
  </section>
  <section id="ID-06baa79251d0ec00517751c983bf8ff6"><title>OPTIONS AND ARGUMENTS</title>
    <para>
      <variablelist>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-a8967fcc30bb001f2350900feb7c03d9" />[<emphasis role="bold">--help</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Print usage and exit.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-3c1c62438ed457c09598171b3fe9c00b" />[<emphasis role="bold">--doctype</emphasis>=<emphasis role="bold">article</emphasis>|<emphasis role="bold">chapter</emphasis>|<emphasis role="bold">section</emphasis>|<emphasis role="bold">refentry</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Specifies the document type for the output file; the default
	      is <emphasis role="bold">section</emphasis>.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-570fbc767342046eb01e3bffde2969f9" />[<emphasis role="bold">--title</emphasis>=<emphasis role="italic">title</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Specifies the document title.  The default is <emphasis
	      role="italic">infile</emphasis>, if it is supplied, or empty
	      string otherwise.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-8d4021783c0a96bedf39327356ca1afc" />[<emphasis role="bold">--spaces</emphasis>=<emphasis role="italic"># spaces per indent level</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Specifies the number of spaces per indent level in the SGML
	      output; the default is 2.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-d23c7a5a0ef01becc3383a41832805d7" />[<emphasis role="bold">--fix-double-quotes</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Replace pairs of double quotes in regular paragraphs with
	      &lt;quote&gt; and &lt;/quote&gt; (see <citerefentry>
	      <refentrytitle>Pod::2::DocBook</refentrytitle>
	      </citerefentry> for details).
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-5e06e9c0f478339bb7cbe9acc5e2b398" />[<emphasis role="bold">--no-header</emphasis>]</term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      Omit the DOCTYPE line from the output.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-0d359410606c76062833b9f11b7aeff6" /><emphasis role="italic">infile</emphasis></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      The name of the file from which to read pod source; if not
	      supplied, STDIN is used for input.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
        <varlistentry>
          <term><anchor id="ID-ecbca8badc8eb33c7394c3d1af24c5e7" /><emphasis role="italic">outfile</emphasis></term>
          <listitem>
            <para>
	      The name of the file to which to write SGML; if not supplied,
	      STDOUT is used for output.
            </para>
          </listitem>
        </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
    </para>
  </section>
